  "text": "TLS configuration in Prometheus flows from configuration definitions in prometheus/prometheus through prometheus-common to the actual tls.Config used in HTTP clients. Here's the complete chain:\n\n## Configuration Definitions (prometheus/prometheus)\n\n1. **prometheus/config/config.go**:\n   - `ScrapeConfig` struct (line 747) contains `HTTPClientConfig` field (line 830), which is inlined from prometheus-common\n   - `RemoteWriteConfig` struct (line 1419) contains `HTTPClientConfig` field (line 1434)\n   - `TracingConfig` struct (line 1160) contains `TLSConfig` field (line 1165) directly from prometheus-common\n\n## TLS Configuration Base Types (prometheus-common)\n\n2. **prometheus-common/config/http_config.go**:\n   - `TLSConfig` struct (line 1199): Defines all TLS configuration fields (CA, CertFile, KeyFile, ServerName, InsecureSkipVerify, MinVersion, MaxVersion, etc.)\n   - `HTTPClientConfig` struct (line 332): Contains `TLSConfig` field (line 346) and other HTTP settings\n   - These types support YAML/JSON unmarshaling and validation\n\n## TLS Configuration Conversion Pipeline\n\n3. **prometheus-common/config/http_config.go** - Key Functions:\n   - `NewTLSConfig` (line 1133): Entry point that delegates to NewTLSConfigWithContext\n   - `NewTLSConfigWithContext` (line 1138): Converts TLSConfig to crypto/tls.Config\n     * Validates the TLSConfig\n     * Creates tls.Config with InsecureSkipVerify, MinVersion, MaxVersion\n     * Reads and parses CA certificates using `updateRootCA` (line 1339)\n     * Sets ServerName\n     * Configures GetClientCertificate callback for client certificates via `getClientCertificate` (line 1302)\n   - `updateRootCA` (line 1339): Parses PEM-encoded CA certificates and updates tls.Config.RootCAs\n   - `getClientCertificate` (line 1302): Loads client certificate and key from files or secrets using tls.X509KeyPair\n\n## HTTP Transport Creation\n\n4. **prometheus-common/config/http_config.go** - RoundTripper Creation:\n   - `NewClientFromConfig` (line 605): Creates http.Client from HTTPClientConfig\n   - `NewRoundTripperFromConfig` (line 622): Creates http.RoundTripper from HTTPClientConfig\n   - `NewRoundTripperFromConfigWithContext` (line 629): Main implementation that:\n     * Calls NewTLSConfigWithContext to create the tls.Config\n     * Passes tls.Config to http.Transport.TLSClientConfig (line 657)\n     * Wraps transport with various middleware (authorization, OAuth2, headers, etc.)\n     * For mutable TLS files, uses NewTLSRoundTripperWithContext for file watching\n   - `tlsRoundTripper` struct (line 1350): Watches for TLS file changes and recreates transport as needed\n   - `NewTLSRoundTripperWithContext` (line 1382): Creates a round tripper that monitors TLS certificate files and reloads them when changed\n\n## Usage in Scrape Targets\n\n5. **prometheus/scrape/scrape.go**:\n   - `newScrapeClient` (line 2260): Called for each scrape target\n   - Calls `config_util.NewClientFromConfig(cfg.HTTPClientConfig, ...)` to create HTTP client\n   - This client uses the TLS configuration from ScrapeConfig.HTTPClientConfig.TLSConfig\n\n## Usage in Remote Write\n\n6. **prometheus/storage/remote/client.go**:\n   - `NewWriteClient` (line 183): Creates HTTP client for remote write\n   - Calls `config_util.NewClientFromConfig(conf.HTTPClientConfig, \"remote_storage_write_client\", ...)`\n   - `NewReadClient` (line 151): Creates HTTP client for remote read\n   - Both use the TLS configuration from RemoteWriteConfig.HTTPClientConfig.TLSConfig\n\n## Usage in Other Components\n\n7. **prometheus/tracing/tracing.go**:\n   - `getClient` (line 179): Uses TLSConfig directly\n   - Calls `config_util.NewTLSConfig(&tracingCfg.TLSConfig)` for gRPC credentials\n   - Used by otlptracegrpc.WithTLSCredentials and otlptracehttp clients\n\n8. **prometheus/notifier/alertmanagerset.go**:\n   - Calls `config_util.NewClientFromConfig(cfg.HTTPClientConfig, \"alertmanager\")` for notification clients\n\n## Validation\n\nThe TLSConfig validation (line 1253) ensures:\n- Only one of ca/ca_file/ca_ref is configured\n- Only one of cert/cert_file/cert_ref is configured\n- Only one of key/key_file/key_ref is configured\n- Client cert and key are paired correctly\n- Min/Max TLS versions are valid\n\nThe HTTPClientConfig validation calls TLSConfig validation as part of its own validation process."
}

